review_blob: This shit is bomb...had at an ole MadCraftBeerWeek and most recently at GTMW15. Crazy hoppy orange juice...probably best dipa ive had...a desert island beer for sure.
Pretty gnarly...not much different from a good BA speedway...but the mouthfeel/palate is take to 11.
beer_name: AleSmith Speedway Stout - Bourbon Barrel Aged: Vietnamese Coffee

review_blob: Had at FOBAB but also last years bottling. Fobab (incredible) / bottle (adjunct-y and meh). Split the difference i guess.
beer_name: Goose Island Bourbon County Stout - Vanilla Rye Barrel

review_blob: GTMW...obviously good, but not crazy. Super coffee and spice aroma...flat black color, taste is supper coffee and spice. Palate is really chalky...not my thing. Would seek out again...but not stand in a fest line...much less trade big.
Tastes like someone mixed Furious and Overrated...except far too malty. Decent hip IPA aroma, but the rest is par. Would not repeat or seek out for the price.
beer_name: Surly / Amager Todd - The Axe Man (Surly Version)

review_blob: Ugh...huge let down.  Looks like breakfast stout...smells sweeter (little wood). Taste is sticky sweetness...regular breakfast stout...gross artificial maple...little wood/booze. Mouthfeel is thick...not as tight as regular of KBS.   By a long shot...CBS < BS < KBS.  A chore that provoked me to rate it.
beer_name: Founders Backstage Series # 2: CBS (Canadian Breakfast Stout)

review_blob: Beautiful beer.  Soft tang, cloves, citrus yeast. Nice looking hefe...though less head. Tastes clean and creamy citrus. Mouthfeel perfect.  Could drink a crap ton. It is good to live in WI.

As with the ELDER...still one beer i dont totally understand the infatuation with...Id rather have a Blind Pig.  Had out of a growler from the most recent release...and from a couple of taps in san diego and oc over the past few years.  not what i look for in a dipa...overly sweet and chalky.  Still pretty good though.
FOBAB 09.  aroma is chocolate, vanilla, and bourbon.  Taste is same with a bit more wood.  heavy silky mouthfeel.  very good.

Ive tried a number of 2006 vintages over the years.  Recent one was perhaps a little past its prime.  Fantastic woody imperial stout aroma.  Poured flat and black...not as thick as regular speedway.  Taste was hurt by a little soy.  Still a great beer.
beer_name: AleSmith Speedway Stout - Bourbon Barrel Aged

review_blob: Old notes from DLD 08.  This beer was great, but only a little better than the 08 darklord.  Aroma and appearance were hurt by plastic cups.  Similar to the standard darklord expect a hair more boozey...noticeable bourbon.
beer_name: Three Floyds Dark Lord Russian Imperial Stout (Bourbon Barrel Aged)

review_blob: UPDATED: APR 24, 2009

I will rate this beer...hear ye hear ye.  Smell is weak...not bad...but not salient or highly perceivable.  Maybe a little hops (citrus...lemons), oxidized malt, and caramel.  Appearance...as all appearances are...throw away category...but it does have nice lacing...tight bubbles and a nice clean burnt amber color.  Palate should be called mouth-feel, as that is what food scientist call it.  Pretty typical for a 3F brew...clean and well carbonated...but with a little oily resin (like a asian snatch waiting to be tamed...citation).  Flavor is candy sweet , with a tad bit of feet-y malt...but it adds a nice body.  Not what I want from a barley wine...but is is quite refreshing and pleasant.  Id rather drink this than go to another 08 DLD!
UPDATED: MAY 14, 2014
Pretty decent.  Color is a hazy orange.  Aroma is pure sour beer...no fruit...much like a gueze.  Flavor is sour with a bit of milky dryness.  Mouthfeel is not quite as dry as most sours.

Pretty bad ass DIPA.  Reminded me a lot of winter yulesmith.  Pours an orange brown with a white head.  Aroma is really spicy and malty...not at all like a huge west coast ipa, but still awesome.  Flavor really brings in some of those citrusy hops while balancing well with the great amount of sweet malt.  Mouthfeel is just about perfect.
beer_name: Tyranena BGW Hop Whore Imperial India Pale Ale

review_blob: This beer was pretty good.  Reddish color with a white head.  Aroma was very earthy...tons of grassy hops, a little bit of citrus, and some dirty malt.  Flavor was similar, except the malt came through more than I expected.  This is very good...it really is kind of a extra bitter woman.
beer_name: Tyranena BGW Bitter Woman From Hell Extra IPA

review_blob:
Cquiroga gave me a taste of this at Port Brewing sometime in Jan.
***Very small sample.
Aroma was huge fresh berry notes...crazily fruity.  Notes of chocolate and roasted malts as well.  Flavor was  largely sweet...a lot going on...but the complexity was in numerous subtleties.  I feel like this would be a great beer to get to know, but on my approx. 4oz...id say that is was very desert like and not at all over powering.  Mouthfeel was light...but that is probably because it is a "baltic porter".

Yikes...dont put a shitty beer in a bourbon barrel...it ends up tasting like bourbon barrel aged shit.  Pours a dark coca cola with a surprisingly thick head.  Aroma is monster wood and smoke...a bit of burnt sugar sweetness and malt too.  It smells like it could actually taste good, but the flavor is completely unbalanced...just massive wood and the beer doesnt stand a chance.  It is also the most difficult to drink 8% beer alcohol wise ive ever encountered.  BOOOOOO.  When I dont finish a beer that costs this much, I know it blows.
beer_name: Goose Island Bourbon Imperial Brown Goose (Bottled)

review_blob: Pours black with no head.  Aroma is big roast and chocolate.  Flavor is quite dry and balanced...the right amount of bitter and sweet, chocolate and coffee, and hardly any alcohol.  Mouthfeel is a bit light.  This is an excellent stout...top 50..probably not.

Pours a pink-honey with a off white head...tight lacing.  Aroma is big spice, sweet yeast, coriander, citrus, malt, and stinky butter.  Flavor is quite bitter and creamy...yeast, orange taffy, pepper, and a bit of stinky caramel.  Mouthfeel is thick and oily...almost dairy like.  Not bad.
***
note...way too much butter....but i dont think this beer has an excuse for being infected...so Ill say its intentional.
UPDATED: MAR 11, 2007

Pours a clear maple red color with a minimal white head.  Aroma is the tops...oakey, sour, fruity, sweet, very little yeast...almost like a jp beer (note: i came up with that without looking at any other reviews).  Flavor is much sweeter than I expected...and not at all like a quad.  It does have some refined creamy spice, oak, honey, and tea flavors...i dont get any bourbon...and I do drink a a fair share of it.  Im wondering if this isnt some sort of franken-quad due the lagering tanks.  Mouthfeel is decent...it matches the flavor well, but then again, the flavor doesnt necessarily match the aroma or style.  I think Id like to try this with some age on it, but i will give it some bonus points for being quite a new beer experience.

Ive fallen off the rating train...and at this point have failed to rate far more beers than I have managed to...but this brew has compelled me to do so.  It is possibly the best smelling beer I have encountered.  Pours a cloudy woody red with a almond head.  Aroma is awesome...definitely a flemish sour, but with a ton of malt sweetness, wood, coconut, cherries, whiskey, almonds, and other fruit.  Flavor is also quite malty of a flemish sour...but brings to mind some sort of mixture between a regular rodenbach and a barrel aged fruit beer.  Mouthfeel is also near perfect for the style.  This is an enigma...this beer kicks ass...and is possibly the most progressive flem sour i have had.

This beer is awesome...and I am sad to see the ratings of JP beers have been declining.    Pours nut brown with a big foamy earthy head.  Aroma is spice and sour...funk and wood.  Flavor is the similar...perfect sweet, sour, wood balance.  Mouthfeel is perfect.
Wicked foreign stout...much like the do dolle extra export stout...except maybe better.

This beer was pretty solid...maybe one of my favorites of the trip...had it at popeyes.  Pours a cloudy chestnut with a milky head and lacing.  Aroma is massive candy sugar, wood, and a bit of scotch.  Flavor is bready yeast, sweet wood, and scotch.  Fairly similar to HoTD Adam.  Medium mouthfeel.

Pours cloudy gold...a small white head...some lacing.  Aroma is belgian yeast and sugar...a little bit of fresh tart fruit.  Flavor is quite fruity...and definitely belgain inspired...not a barley wine.   Some yeast and apple...the alcohol is well hidden...it clearly says 12% on the bottle.  The mouthfeel is a bit flat...but still good.

Pours a cloudy pinkish orange with a thick yolk colored head...sticky lacing.   Aroma is yeast and vegetables...maybe a bit of dairy and hops.  Flavor is yeast and oranges...dairy and vegetables...and incredibly dry.  Really not a belgian at all...so im not sure what that is about...it is somewhere between a weak old ale and a bizarro barley wine vegetable beer.  Mouthfeel is actually quite heavy...and creamy...which adds a great balance to this beer.

Pours pretty black with a minimal tan head.  Aroma is burnt malt, light chocolate, maybe a bit of socky candy.  Flavor is a bit of smokey malt, cream, mild bitterness, and acidic fruit.  Mouthfeel is chalky and creamy.
beer_name: Iwate Kura Kaki No Stout (Oyster Stout)

review_blob: Pours a dark chestnut...with a cloudy mocha head.  Aroma is grass, milk chocolate, vanilla, and some caramel malt.  Flavor is a bit acidic...with chocolate and strawberries...kind of like a less intense foriegn stout...this isnt bad at all...and i disagree with those that think the kirin is better.  and whoever gave it a .5 was off his rocker.  Mouthfeel is kind of watery, but it has a oily slickness that makes it acceptable.

Pours dark brown...with a bit of red and a huge mocha head.  Aroma is milk chocolate, nuts, and a bit of strawberry.  Flavor is a chalky chocolate and coffee...a little bit of fruit juice sweetness and some bitter paper taste.  Mouthfeel is a bit watery.
UPDATED: JUN 16, 2008

Pours quite black with a light mocha head...decent lacing.  Aroma is a bit of coffee...molasses...caramel malt...and burnt leather.  Flavor is quite smokey...a little bit of sock tasting malt...and a bit of spice...maybe this was "lost in translation", but I think it should be a smoked porter.  Mouthfeel is light for a porter.

Pour is dark chestnut with a thick tan head.  Aroma is crazy spicey...cinnamon and other christmas potpourri shit.  Flavor is similar...but with some belgian candy sugar and some sweet bready yeasty malt.  Mouthfeel is kind of carbonated and a bit light.

amber orange pour with a soft white head.  nose is sweet caramel and some hops.  Flavor is creamy malt, caramel, and earthy hops...a bit dirty though...this beer is really sweet too...not really sure why most of these ji-biru are so sweet.  Mouthfeel is quite carbonated.

Pours light yellow...no head.  Aroma is monster artificial apricot and sugar.  Flavor is similar...except there is a bit of milk and caramel.  This beer is for girls.  Mouthfeel is syrupy.  This doesnt taste that bad...but it is hard to drink...sugar water.  Maybe be good to pour over fruit for desert.

Pours rosey orange red...with no head.  Aroma is alcohol (brandy), sweet malts, spice, and grass.  Flavor is woody, dirty malt, alcohol (brandy), paper, and a bit of starch.  Mouthfeel is incredibly carbonated and oily.  not bad, but not great...there are better japanese barley wines out there.

2006...courtesy of zebracakes...live in tokyo.  Pours a bit of cloudy coca cola...with a light tan head.  Aroma is a bit of sour malt and a bit of funky fruit.  Flavor is similar...subtle, but balanced...there is also some notes of higher alcohol...quite tasty.  Mouthfeel is medium and a pretty sweet dryness.

Pours a bit more cloudy than typical kolsch.  Smells like a bit of peppery yeast and corn syrup...chemical alcohol and milk.  Flavor is pretty much fruity (citrus and cream) and ricey...a little bit of juice to make it sweet...and definitely doesnt have enough dryness.  But then again...it doesnt taste that much worse than all the klsch I had in kln for a day and a half.

Pours amber orange...decent head.  Aroma is moderate vanilla and fruit juice...sweet malt...way more alcohol than expected.  Flavor is a bit like orange and a some malt...a little bit of chemical vanilla...very dry from the yeast.  Mouthfeel is very watery...could have used a bit more.

Pours like a pale lager...though a lot of carbonation and a thicker head.  Aroma is slightly sweet yeast and nothing else. Flavor is sugary and syrupy...not really much else...a bit of dry yeast and maybe a tad bit of grass.  Body is actually semi creamy and much more thick than an average pale lager.

This brewery is called morita kinshachi beer.  This was a decent pilsener...so says the bottle.  Pours like a light pale lager.   Slightly peppery aroma and a bit of rice and sweetness.  Taste is water.  Finish is sweet and dry.  Pretty much just a glorified bud.

aroma is slightly sweet...bit of peppery yeast...not too much else.  Looks like a pale lager with a nicer head.  Flavor is slightly sweet with fruit juice and simple syrup.  Also a fair amount of pepper and dryness from yeast.  Mouthfeel is watery.

Im not sure if it is a sweet stout, my japanese friend said it says it is a porter.  aroma is milky and slightly chocolate.  Flavor is subtle creamy chocolate and a little bit of bitterness.  Mouthfeel is a bit milky and watery...but fine for a porter or sweet stout i guess...this is one the better ji-birus ive had on my trip.
aroma like a citrusy amber with a bit of yeast.  looks like a golden macro.  flavor is very sweet and a bit like coopers cream ale.  mouthfeel is watery.  pretty good but too sweet.

06 bottle... this beer is pretty good.  pours black with minimal head.  aroma is big chocolate and fruity imp stout...no bourbon.  Flavor is also very good...kind of like a central waters barrel stout when it is on.  However, there is little if any true bourbon flavor in this beer...which was surprising.  True there was some wood and vanilla, but I was expecting more.   Mouthfeel was just about damn perfect for an imp stout...creamy and thick.

interesting...on tap at the wrigleyville location.  Just had the regular bourbon the day prior...and i enjoyed it much more.  10 oz  black pour with no head.  Aroma is big chocolate and subdued coffee.  Taste is similar...except it is lacking some intensity...quite balanced...except it doesnt have that imperial feel.  If you think this has any bourbon or wood in it...you dont drink bourbon much.  Mouthfeel is huge and thick...perhaps the heaviest Ive encountered.
beer_name: Goose Island Bourbon County Stout - Coffee

review_blob: not bad...pours hazy pink gold with big hay colored head.  Aroma is sweet and big...not very saisonish.  Flavor is much more like a sweet belgian strong ale...looses a lot of the farmhouse...but it is still a bit dry...and has a bunch of spice to add to the tastiness of this brew.  Mouthfeel is medium and a bit carbonated.

This beer is remarkable...easily my favorite dipa.  color orange with a big cake-y head.  aroma is huge citrusy hops and a hint of sweet spice and yeast.  flavor is similar, but huge and balanced and creamy...perfect.
